President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing the importance of the health and safety of farmers, ranchers, and foresters during National Farm Safety and Health Week. The proclamation acknowledges the risks that agricultural workers face on a daily basis, such as operating heavy machinery and navigating harsh weather conditions. It highlights the need to improve safety practices and adopt innovative technologies to reduce risks. The administration is committed to providing farmers with the tools, training, and resources they need to remain both productive and healthy. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to reaffirm their dedication to farm safety and health and to express their appreciation and gratitude to farmers, ranchers, and foresters for their contributions to the nation. National Farm Safety and Health Week is proclaimed to be observed from September 15 to September 21, 2019.